\n

Create zip of web page

\n

Create an archive of your website, containing all needed documents.

\n

Put zipped data somewhere

\n
    \n
  • Put the file in any of web-based file storages, like\n cloudooo.com, Google docs, etc.
    • \n
  • Note URL which allow access to raw (not formatted)\n data, it will be used later.
    • \n
\n

Put this archive somewhere (Cloudooo, Google Docs, â€¦), and note the URL to access raw data

\n

Configure webrunner (1)

\n
    \n
  • Configure git repository: Home->Create
    • \n
  • URL is: http://git.erp5.org/repos/slapos.git
    • \n
  • Name/email are not important
    • \n
\n

When you connect to the webrunner for the first time, it will ask you some informations. select "http://git.erp5.org/repos/slapos.git" as git repository. Put dummy name and email if necessary.

\n

Configure webrunner (2)

\n

Then, go back to webrunner home page, click on "open existing project".

\n

Configure webrunner (3)

\n

Then, go back to webrunner home page, click on "open existing project", select software/lamp-template-static and click on the "Open software" button. It will redirect you to the software profile edition page.

\n

Customize software profile

\n

You need to change application:url. Example follow in next slide. http://www.slapos.org/slapos-Lecture.Telecom.Static.Site/Base_download

\n

Filled software profile

\n

Here you can see filled profile.

\n

Install software

\n

As soon as software and instance profiles are provided it is time to build the software.

\n

Students are responsible to debug the software build process and fix issues until no error will be found in software build log.

\n

Run the instance

\n

Now it is time to instantiate

\n

Inspect to know to connect

\n

Now it is time to inspect the instance, in order to know how to connect.

\n

SlapOS powered web site

\n

After successful instantiation it is possible to access your website.

\n

Stop the instance

\n

In order to finish the work and free the resources it is good to stop the instance.
